f; font-size: 12pt;\">4.0km Go right just before the 3km marker. Left goes to Wragge Beach on Slocan Lake and the Wragge Beach Recreation Site with several campsites (fees). Can also access Wragge Lake.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">6km Branch 6. Stay right on the main road.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">12km road marker. Go right. Left goes to Huss Creek, the Shannon Lake Trail and Mt Vingolf (look for a brown, 4&#215;4 post with white lettering, signed &#8220;Shannon Lake&#8221;).<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">14.35km Go right to Big Sister and Rugged. Left continues to Caribou Pass. \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">15.4km Go left on the worst road (grassy).<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">17.05km Hairpin. Go left\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">18.15km Park past the Valhalla Mountain Touring Lodge at 6500&#8242;.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Route:<\/strong>\u00a0Climb Rugged first. There isn&#8217;t a trail but follow a steep avalanche chute straight up to the base of Rugged Peak. Scramble to the top. Descend 500 feet to the col between Rugged and Big Sister and climb Big Sister up the west ridge. Return down this ridge to the cars.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>RUGGED PEAK\u00a08000&#8242; BIG SISTER PEAK\u00a0 8093&#8242; These are the impressive peaks on the right visible from the highway between Summit Lake and Slocan Lake. \u00a0 Difficulty: Elevation gained: Key Elevations: Distance: Time: Season: July to September Map: 82F\/4 Nakusp Drive:\u00a0Shannon &hellip; <a href=\"